#BOOM! So now I'm 14 weeks post surgery! After a Patellar tendon rupture it's been a learning process to say the least. Knowing how to keep me ego in check in order to push it juuust enough to recover. As you can see in the top picture, visually they are almost equal as I'm just missing a little separation. Left knee a bit swollen. On the @dexabody scan, it shows I actually have equal muscle and fat balance!! #FuckinBoom!! My protocols have been on point! Methods have been #ketosis #kaatsu #TheMarcPro #ketoOS and phenomenal soft tissue work from @mardenjared and @chirofusionutah, with @uscryo_saltlakecity to top it all off! When the original day I went in for surgery on Jenny 29th, the nurse told me that I would lose all of my muscle in my left leg! That I would have zero quad left. And it would be a long arduous process to get it back. I said, fuck that! I will be back in less than 12 weeks! This dexa was 2 weeks ago. #science #fueledbyketoOS #superman #Superhero #theSuperheroMakers #fit #fitspo #fitfam #recoveryKing #ketoKingandQueen #ketoLife #ketogains #coach #nutritionist #expert #fuckyeah
